Here are its key features: AI job matching & alerts: 
Jobright continuously scans its job database (claimed 400K+ new postings daily) and suggests roles that fit your skills and experience. 
You can set preferences (titles, location, salary) and get early alerts on new jobs that match

Looking into Jobright.ai to automate your job search? You’re not alone.

With promises of AI job matching, resume tailoring, and auto-apply features, it’s quickly gained attention – but is it actually worth your time (or money)?

In this article, we’ll break down what Jobright offers, how it works, and what real users are saying about it.

And if you’re here to find the best alternative, you might want to jump to our comparison with JobCopilot to understand why it’s currently the stronger option for hands-free job applications.

What is Jobright?
Jobright is an AI-powered platform that helps job seekers automate their job search. It matches you to open roles based on your resume, then helps you apply faster with AI-optimized resumes and insider referrals. The platform focuses on reducing manual work — from finding jobs to sending applications — using a mix of automation and smart recommendations.

